article.description: Markquis Nowell had 26 points as Arkansas-Little Rock got past Alcorn State 67-50 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Nowell scores 26 to lead UALR over Alcorn St. 67-50
article.linkText: Nowell scores 26 to lead UALR over Alcorn St. 67-50
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Markquis Nowell had 26 points as Arkansas-Little Rock got past Alcorn State 67-50 on Wednesday night. Nowell also had eight turnovers but only two assists. Kamani Johnson had 17 points and 12 rebounds for Arkansas-Little Rock (5-3). Jovan Stulic added 11 points and six rebounds. Ruot Monyyong had 12 rebounds for the home team. Troymain Crosby had 19 points and nine rebounds for the Braves (2-5). Maurice Howard added 13 points. Deshaw Andrews had eight rebounds. Arkansas-Little Rock matches up against East Tennessee State at home on Saturday. Alcorn State plays Blue Mountain College at home next Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
